      "description": "Available is a 2008 BMW M3 (E92) featuring the high-revving, naturally aspirated S65 4.0L V8 engine. This unit maintains excellent compression across all eight cylinders, with the individual throttle bodies providing instantaneous transient response up to the 8,400 RPM redline. The 6-speed manual gearbox offers tactile shift gates, paired with a Variable M Differential Lock for superior corner-exit traction. The chassis is equipped with Electronic Damper Control (EDC) and remains neutral thanks to a well-sorted multi-link rear geometry. Recent preventive maintenance includes a throttle actuator refresh and a comprehensive VANOS system inspection. A mechanically sound example of the final naturally aspirated M3, ready for spirited driving.",
